        The founder of Whitenicious is Cameroonian pop star Denecia.
    
        
There has been controversy around her brand since it launched in 2014. In an interview with Ebony at the time, she was quoted as saying: "Will Whitenicious bleach your skin if you use it on all your skin? Yes, it will. Are we selling Whitenicous for that purpose? No, we're not."The company says its cream is meant to be used for conditions like hyperpigmentation, when people have dark spots on their skin. But that hasn't stopped a backlash against Blac Chyna, who rose to fame stripping and modelling, before launching a make-up brand and having a child with Rob Kardashian.
    
        
            Skip Instagram post  by whitenicious
                    View this post on Instagram           Looking At The Bright Side Of Our Faces.  #blacchyna #skincare #facecare A post shared by  Whitenicious By Dencia (@whitenicious) on Nov 19, 2018 at 11:20am PST
